# Google Spreadsheet Translator - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
This is a Google Apps Script extension for translating spreadsheet content with a custom sidebar interface.

## Project Structure
- `src/Code.gs` - Server-side Google Apps Script logic
- `src/Sidebar.html` - Main HTML template with Google Apps Script includes
- `src/Stylesheet.html` - CSS styles for the sidebar interface
- `src/Javascript.html` - Client-side JavaScript functionality
- `src/appsscript.json` - Google Apps Script project configuration
- `.clasp.json` - Clasp CLI configuration for deployment
- `build-test.js` - Local development build script

## Development Guidelines

### Google Apps Script Development
- Use `<?!= include('Filename'); ?>` syntax for including separate HTML files
- Server-side functions in `Code.gs` should be prefixed with appropriate naming
- Client-side communication uses `google.script.run` with proper error handling

### File Organization
- Keep HTML, CSS, and JavaScript in separate files for maintainability
- Use the build script (`build-test.js`) for local development testing
- Maintain consistent naming conventions across all files

### Code Standards
- Use modern JavaScript (ES6+) features where supported
- Implement proper error handling with try-catch blocks
- Use CSS classes instead of inline styles for better maintainability
- Follow Google Apps Script best practices for performance

### Deployment
- Use `clasp push` to deploy changes to Google Apps Script
- Test locally using the build script before deploying
- Ensure all file extensions are properly configured in `.clasp.json`

## Notes
- The project uses Google Apps Script's HTML templating system
- Local development requires the build script to merge separate files
- Flag icons are loaded from CDN for language selection
- The interface includes advanced settings and help overlay functionality
